<section xml:id="section-linear-indep-terminology">

<title>Terminology and notation</title>

<p><dl>

	<li xml:id="definition-linear-dep">
	<title>linearly dependent set of vectors</title>
	<idx><h>linearly</h><h>dependent</h></idx>
	<p>
	a set of vectors in which there is at least one example of a vector that can be expressed as a linear combination of other vectors in the set;
	we also consider the set of vectors consisting of <em>only</em> the zero vector as linearly dependent
	</p>
	</li>

	<li xml:id="definition-linear-indep">
	<title>linearly independent set of vectors</title>
	<idx><h>linearly</h><h>independent</h></idx>
	<p>
	a set of vectors that is not linearly dependent;
	that is, a set of vectors in which <em>no</em> vector can be expressed as a linear combination of other vectors in the set
	</p>
	</li>

</dl></p>

</section>
